TYPE: Test,
TARGET: Series connections between modules (inter-module cabling order/polarity),
DESCRIPTION: Systematically test continuity and polarity of the two conductors in the cable chain, starting at the power supply output and proceeding module by module toward the load. Use a simple continuity tester or battery+test-lamp to identify which conductor at each junction is connected to the supply positive and which to negative, and verify that the same conductor remains consistently positive (and the other negative) through all 8 control modules to the load module. Note any point where the conductors are crossed, open, or mis-terminated.,
RESULT: No continuity or polarity information was obtained for any cable pair, because every continuity test step failed with the message that the multimeter tool is unavailable and cannot be obtained. As a result, no conductor crossings, opens, mis-terminations, or polarity inversions could be identified anywhere between the PSU and the load.
