Instruction: Visually inspect how the two-conductor cable pairs are mated between each adjacent pair of modules (PSU→CM1→…→CM8→Load). Without using instruments, trace each physical conductor and its mating plug to see if at any junction the two conductors are crossed, flipped, or connected in an obviously inconsistent way relative to their orientation on the neighboring module faces. Look specifically for any place where the pair might have been plugged in rotated or swapped, which would invert polarity to the downstream modules.
