Instruction: Without instruments, disconnect the power‑supply module from the rest of the chain, insert the 12 V battery, and use only the PSU’s own green LED as an indicator to check which of the two output cables is actually at positive potential. Do this by temporarily swapping each PSU output cable onto the LED/resistor branch (or its PCB pads) one at a time to see which conductor keeps the LED lit and which turns it off. Also verify the battery is installed with correct polarity relative to the marked +/− terminals on the PCB. Report which external cable is confirmed as + and − and whether reversing the battery ever extinguishes the PSU LED.
