RESULT: The PSU module panel could not be opened, but internal connections were inspected via the enclosure. The battery’s positive terminal is not connected to any cable, while the battery negative terminal is connected to PSU Output Cable (−); PSU Output Cable (+) and PSU Output Cable (−) each loop back onto themselves and feed their respective control input cables. The green LED is connected only from its cathode to PSU Output Cable (−), and the series resistor is connected only from its positive side to PSU Output Cable (+), with their other ends unconnected.
